AddBandingRequest.name: AddBandingRequest
AddBandingRequest.description: Adds a new banded range to the spreadsheet.

AddBandingResponse.name: AddBandingResponse
AddBandingResponse.description: The result of adding a banded range.

AddChartRequest.name: AddChartRequest
AddChartRequest.description: Adds a chart to a sheet in the spreadsheet.

AddChartResponse.name: AddChartResponse
AddChartResponse.description: The result of adding a chart to a spreadsheet.

AddConditionalFormatRuleRequest.name: AddConditionalFormatRuleRequest
AddConditionalFormatRuleRequest.description:
Adds a new conditional format rule at the given index.
All subsequent rules' indexes are incremented.

index.name: index
index.description: The zero-based index where the rule should be inserted.

AddFilterViewResponse.name: AddFilterViewResponse
AddFilterViewResponse.description: The result of adding a filter view.

AddNamedRangeRequest.name: AddNamedRangeRequest
AddNamedRangeRequest.description: Adds a named range to the spreadsheet.

AddNamedRangeResponse.name: AddNamedRangeResponse
AddNamedRangeResponse.description: The result of adding a named range.

AddProtectedRangeResponse.name: AddProtectedRangeResponse
AddProtectedRangeResponse.description: The result of adding a new protected range.

AddSheetRequest.name: AddSheetRequest
AddSheetRequest.description:
Adds a new sheet.
When a sheet is added at a given index,
all subsequent sheets' indexes are incremented.
To add an object sheet, use AddChartRequest instead and specify
EmbeddedObjectPosition.sheetId or
EmbeddedObjectPosition.newSheet.

AddSheetResponse.name: AddSheetResponse
AddSheetResponse.description: The result of adding a sheet.

AppendCellsRequest.name: AppendCellsRequest
AppendCellsRequest.description:
Adds new cells after the last row with data in a sheet,
inserting new rows into the sheet if necessary.

sheetId.name: sheetId
sheetId.description: The sheet ID to append the data to.

fields.name: fields
fields.description:
The fields of CellData that should be updated.
At least one field must be specified.
The root is the CellData; 'row.values.' should not be specified.
A single `"*"` can be used as short-hand for listing every field.

AppendDimensionRequest.name: AppendDimensionRequest
AppendDimensionRequest.description: Appends rows or columns to the end of a sheet.

length.name: length
length.description: The number of rows or columns to append.

sheetId.name: sheetId
sheetId.description: The sheet to append rows or columns to.

dimension.name: dimension
dimension.description: Whether rows or columns should be appended.

AppendValuesResponse.name: AppendValuesResponse
AppendValuesResponse.description: The response when updating a range of values in a spreadsheet.

spreadsheetId.name: spreadsheetId
spreadsheetId.description: The spreadsheet the updates were applied to.

tableRange.name: tableRange
tableRange.description:
The range (in A1 notation) of the table that values are being appended to
(before the values were appended).
Empty if no table was found.

AutoFillRequest.name: AutoFillRequest
AutoFillRequest.description: Fills in more data based on existing data.

useAlternateSeries.name: useAlternateSeries
useAlternateSeries.description:
True if we should generate data with the "alternate" series.
This differs based on the type and amount of source data.

AutoResizeDimensionsRequest.name: AutoResizeDimensionsRequest
AutoResizeDimensionsRequest.description:
Automatically resizes one or more dimensions based on the contents
of the cells in that dimension.

BandedRange.name: BandedRange
BandedRange.description: A banded (alternating colors) range in a sheet.

bandedRangeId.name: bandedRangeId
bandedRangeId.description: The id of the banded range.

BandingProperties.name: BandingProperties
BandingProperties.description:
Properties referring a single dimension (either row or column). If both
BandedRange.row_properties and BandedRange.column_properties are
set, the fill colors are applied to cells according to the following rules:

* header_color and footer_color take priority over band colors.
* first_band_color takes priority over second_band_color.
* row_properties takes priority over column_properties.

For example, the first row color takes priority over the first column
color, but the first column color takes priority over the second row color.
Similarly, the row header takes priority over the column header in the
top left cell, but the column header takes priority over the first row
color if the row header is not set.

BasicChartAxis.name: BasicChartAxis
BasicChartAxis.description:
An axis of the chart.
A chart may not have more than one axis per
axis position.

title.name: title
title.description:
The title of this axis. If set, this overrides any title inferred
from headers of the data.

BasicChartDomain.name: BasicChartDomain
BasicChartDomain.description:
The domain of a chart.
For example, if charting stock prices over time, this would be the date.

BasicChartSeries.name: BasicChartSeries
BasicChartSeries.description:
A single series of data in a chart.
For example, if charting stock prices over time, multiple series may exist,
one for the "Open Price", "High Price", "Low Price" and "Close Price".

targetAxis.name: targetAxis
targetAxis.description:
The minor axis that will specify the range of values for this series.
For example, if charting stocks over time, the "Volume" series
may want to be pinned to the right with the prices pinned to the left,
because the scale of trading volume is different than the scale of
prices.
It is an error to specify an axis that isn't a valid minor axis
for the chart's type.

type.name: type
type.description:
The type of this series. Valid only if the
chartType is
COMBO.
Different types will change the way the series is visualized.
Only LINE, AREA,
and COLUMN are supported.

BasicChartSpec.name: BasicChartSpec
BasicChartSpec.description:
The specification for a basic chart.  See BasicChartType for the list
of charts this supports.

series.name: series
series.description: The data this chart is visualizing.

domains.name: domains
domains.description:
The domain of data this is charting.
Only a single domain is currently supported.

headerCount.name: headerCount
headerCount.description:
The number of rows or columns in the data that are "headers".
If not set, Google Sheets will guess how many rows are headers based
on the data.

(Note that BasicChartAxis.title may override the axis title
 inferred from the header values.)

legendPosition.name: legendPosition
legendPosition.description: The position of the chart legend.

BasicFilter.name: BasicFilter
BasicFilter.description: The default filter associated with a sheet.

sortSpecs.name: sortSpecs
sortSpecs.description:
The sort order per column. Later specifications are used when values
are equal in the earlier specifications.

criteria.name: criteria
criteria.description:
The criteria for showing/hiding values per column.
The map's key is the column index, and the value is the criteria for
that column.

BatchClearValuesRequest.name: BatchClearValuesRequest
BatchClearValuesRequest.description: The request for clearing more than one range of values in a spreadsheet.

ranges.name: ranges
ranges.description: The ranges to clear, in A1 notation.

BatchClearValuesResponse.name: BatchClearValuesResponse
BatchClearValuesResponse.description: The response when updating a range of values in a spreadsheet.

clearedRanges.name: clearedRanges
clearedRanges.description:
The ranges that were cleared, in A1 notation.
(If the requests were for an unbounded range or a ranger larger
 than the bounds of the sheet, this will be the actual ranges
 that were cleared, bounded to the sheet's limits.)

spreadsheetId.name: spreadsheetId
spreadsheetId.description: The spreadsheet the updates were applied to.

BatchGetValuesResponse.name: BatchGetValuesResponse
BatchGetValuesResponse.description: The response when retrieving more than one range of values in a spreadsheet.

valueRanges.name: valueRanges
valueRanges.description:
The requested values. The order of the ValueRanges is the same as the
order of the requested ranges.

spreadsheetId.name: spreadsheetId
spreadsheetId.description: The ID of the spreadsheet the data was retrieved from.

BatchUpdateSpreadsheetRequest.name: BatchUpdateSpreadsheetRequest
BatchUpdateSpreadsheetRequest.description: The request for updating any aspect of a spreadsheet.

requests.name: requests
requests.description: A list of updates to apply to the spreadsheet.

BatchUpdateSpreadsheetResponse.name: BatchUpdateSpreadsheetResponse
BatchUpdateSpreadsheetResponse.description: The reply for batch updating a spreadsheet.

replies.name: replies
replies.description:
The reply of the updates.  This maps 1:1 with the updates, although
replies to some requests may be empty.

spreadsheetId.name: spreadsheetId
spreadsheetId.description: The spreadsheet the updates were applied to.

BatchUpdateValuesRequest.name: BatchUpdateValuesRequest
BatchUpdateValuesRequest.description: The request for updating more than one range of values in a spreadsheet.

valueInputOption.name: valueInputOption
valueInputOption.description: How the input data should be interpreted.

data.name: data
data.description: The new values to apply to the spreadsheet.

BatchUpdateValuesResponse.name: BatchUpdateValuesResponse
BatchUpdateValuesResponse.description: The response when updating a range of values in a spreadsheet.

totalUpdatedColumns.name: totalUpdatedColumns
totalUpdatedColumns.description:
The total number of columns where at least one cell in the column was
updated.

totalUpdatedCells.name: totalUpdatedCells
totalUpdatedCells.description: The total number of cells updated.

totalUpdatedRows.name: totalUpdatedRows
totalUpdatedRows.description: The total number of rows where at least one cell in the row was updated.

responses.name: responses
responses.description:
One UpdateValuesResponse per requested range, in the same order as
the requests appeared.

spreadsheetId.name: spreadsheetId
spreadsheetId.description: The spreadsheet the updates were applied to.

totalUpdatedSheets.name: totalUpdatedSheets
totalUpdatedSheets.description:
The total number of sheets where at least one cell in the sheet was
updated.

BooleanCondition.name: BooleanCondition
BooleanCondition.description:
A condition that can evaluate to true or false.
BooleanConditions are used by conditional formatting,
data validation, and the criteria in filters.

values.name: values
values.description:
The values of the condition. The number of supported values depends
on the condition type.  Some support zero values,
others one or two values,
and ConditionType.ONE_OF_LIST supports an arbitrary number of values.

BooleanRule.name: BooleanRule
BooleanRule.description: A rule that may or may not match, depending on the condition.

width.name: width
width.description:
The width of the border, in pixels.
Deprecated; the width is determined by the "style" field.

hyperlink.name: hyperlink
hyperlink.description:
A hyperlink this cell points to, if any.
This field is read-only.  (To set it, use a `=HYPERLINK` formula.)

formattedValue.name: formattedValue
formattedValue.description:
The formatted value of the cell.
This is the value as it's shown to the user.
This field is read-only.

textFormatRuns.name: textFormatRuns
textFormatRuns.description:
Runs of rich text applied to subsections of the cell.  Runs are only valid
on user entered strings, not formulas, bools, or numbers.
Runs start at specific indexes in the text and continue until the next
run. Properties of a run will continue unless explicitly changed
in a subsequent run (and properties of the first run will continue
the properties of the cell unless explicitly changed).

When writing, the new runs will overwrite any prior runs.  When writing a
new user_entered_value, previous runs will be erased.

textDirection.name: textDirection
textDirection.description: The direction of the text in the cell.

horizontalAlignment.name: horizontalAlignment
horizontalAlignment.description: The horizontal alignment of the value in the cell.

wrapStrategy.name: wrapStrategy
wrapStrategy.description: The wrap strategy for the value in the cell.

hyperlinkDisplayType.name: hyperlinkDisplayType
hyperlinkDisplayType.description: How a hyperlink, if it exists, should be displayed in the cell.

verticalAlignment.name: verticalAlignment
verticalAlignment.description: The vertical alignment of the value in the cell.

ChartData.name: ChartData
ChartData.description: The data included in a domain or series.

sources.name: sources
sources.description:
The ranges of data for a series or domain.
Exactly one dimension must have a length of 1,
and all sources in the list must have the same dimension
with length 1.
The domain (if it exists) & all series must have the same number
of source ranges. If using more than one source range, then the source
range at a given offset must be contiguous across the domain and series.

For example, these are valid configurations:

    domain sources: A1:A5
    series1 sources: B1:B5
    series2 sources: D6:D10

    domain sources: A1:A5, C10:C12
    series1 sources: B1:B5, D10:D12
    series2 sources: C1:C5, E10:E12

hiddenDimensionStrategy.name: hiddenDimensionStrategy
hiddenDimensionStrategy.description: Determines how the charts will use hidden rows or columns.

ClearBasicFilterRequest.name: ClearBasicFilterRequest
ClearBasicFilterRequest.description: Clears the basic filter, if any exists on the sheet.

sheetId.name: sheetId
sheetId.description: The sheet ID on which the basic filter should be cleared.

ClearValuesRequest.name: ClearValuesRequest
ClearValuesRequest.description: The request for clearing a range of values in a spreadsheet.

ClearValuesResponse.name: ClearValuesResponse
ClearValuesResponse.description: The response when clearing a range of values in a spreadsheet.

clearedRange.name: clearedRange
clearedRange.description:
The range (in A1 notation) that was cleared.
(If the request was for an unbounded range or a ranger larger
 than the bounds of the sheet, this will be the actual range
 that was cleared, bounded to the sheet's limits.)

spreadsheetId.name: spreadsheetId
spreadsheetId.description: The spreadsheet the updates were applied to.

Color.name: Color

red.name: red
red.description: The amount of red in the color as a value in the interval [0, 1].

green.name: green
green.description: The amount of green in the color as a value in the interval [0, 1].

blue.name: blue
blue.description: The amount of blue in the color as a value in the interval [0, 1].

alpha.name: alpha
alpha.description:
The fraction of this color that should be applied to the pixel. That is,
the final pixel color is defined by the equation:

  pixel color = alpha * (this color) + (1.0 - alpha) * (background color)

This means that a value of 1.0 corresponds to a solid color, whereas
a value of 0.0 corresponds to a completely transparent color. This
uses a wrapper message rather than a simple float scalar so that it is
possible to distinguish between a default value and the value being unset.
If omitted, this color object is to be rendered as a solid color
(as if the alpha value had been explicitly given with a value of 1.0).

relativeDate.name: relativeDate
relativeDate.description:
A relative date (based on the current date).
Valid only if the type is
DATE_BEFORE,
DATE_AFTER,
DATE_ON_OR_BEFORE or
DATE_ON_OR_AFTER.

Relative dates are not supported in data validation.
They are supported only in conditional formatting and
conditional filters.

userEnteredValue.name: userEnteredValue
userEnteredValue.description:
A value the condition is based on.
The value will be parsed as if the user typed into a cell.
Formulas are supported (and must begin with an `=`).

ConditionalFormatRule.name: ConditionalFormatRule
ConditionalFormatRule.description: A rule describing a conditional format.

ranges.name: ranges
ranges.description:
The ranges that will be formatted if the condition is true.
All the ranges must be on the same grid.

CopyPasteRequest.name: CopyPasteRequest
CopyPasteRequest.description: Copies data from the source to the destination.

pasteType.name: pasteType
pasteType.description: What kind of data to paste.

pasteOrientation.name: pasteOrientation
pasteOrientation.description: How that data should be oriented when pasting.

CopySheetToAnotherSpreadsheetRequest.name: CopySheetToAnotherSpreadsheetRequest
CopySheetToAnotherSpreadsheetRequest.description: The request to copy a sheet across spreadsheets.

destinationSpreadsheetId.name: destinationSpreadsheetId
destinationSpreadsheetId.description: The ID of the spreadsheet to copy the sheet to.

CutPasteRequest.name: CutPasteRequest
CutPasteRequest.description: Moves data from the source to the destination.

pasteType.name: pasteType
pasteType.description:
What kind of data to paste.  All the source data will be cut, regardless
of what is pasted.

inputMessage.name: inputMessage
inputMessage.description: A message to show the user when adding data to the cell.

showCustomUi.name: showCustomUi
showCustomUi.description:
True if the UI should be customized based on the kind of condition.
If true, "List" conditions will show a dropdown.

strict.name: strict
strict.description: True if invalid data should be rejected.

DeleteBandingRequest.name: DeleteBandingRequest
DeleteBandingRequest.description: Removes the banded range with the given ID from the spreadsheet.

bandedRangeId.name: bandedRangeId
bandedRangeId.description: The ID of the banded range to delete.

DeleteConditionalFormatRuleRequest.name: DeleteConditionalFormatRuleRequest
DeleteConditionalFormatRuleRequest.description:
Deletes a conditional format rule at the given index.
All subsequent rules' indexes are decremented.

sheetId.name: sheetId
sheetId.description: The sheet the rule is being deleted from.

index.name: index
index.description: The zero-based index of the rule to be deleted.

DeleteConditionalFormatRuleResponse.name: DeleteConditionalFormatRuleResponse
DeleteConditionalFormatRuleResponse.description: The result of deleting a conditional format rule.

DeleteDimensionRequest.name: DeleteDimensionRequest
DeleteDimensionRequest.description: Deletes the dimensions from the sheet.

DeleteEmbeddedObjectRequest.name: DeleteEmbeddedObjectRequest
DeleteEmbeddedObjectRequest.description: Deletes the embedded object with the given ID.

objectId.name: objectId
objectId.description: The ID of the embedded object to delete.

filterId.name: filterId
filterId.description: The ID of the filter to delete.

DeleteNamedRangeRequest.name: DeleteNamedRangeRequest
DeleteNamedRangeRequest.description: Removes the named range with the given ID from the spreadsheet.

namedRangeId.name: namedRangeId
namedRangeId.description: The ID of the named range to delete.

DeleteProtectedRangeRequest.name: DeleteProtectedRangeRequest
DeleteProtectedRangeRequest.description: Deletes the protected range with the given ID.

protectedRangeId.name: protectedRangeId
protectedRangeId.description: The ID of the protected range to delete.

sheetId.name: sheetId
sheetId.description: The ID of the sheet to delete.

hiddenByUser.name: hiddenByUser
hiddenByUser.description: True if this dimension is explicitly hidden.

hiddenByFilter.name: hiddenByFilter
hiddenByFilter.description:
True if this dimension is being filtered.
This field is read-only.

pixelSize.name: pixelSize
pixelSize.description: The height (if a row) or width (if a column) of the dimension in pixels.

DimensionRange.name: DimensionRange
DimensionRange.description:
A range along a single dimension on a sheet.
All indexes are zero-based.
Indexes are half open: the start index is inclusive
and the end index is exclusive.
Missing indexes indicate the range is unbounded on that side.

startIndex.name: startIndex
startIndex.description: The start (inclusive) of the span, or not set if unbounded.

endIndex.name: endIndex
endIndex.description: The end (exclusive) of the span, or not set if unbounded.

sheetId.name: sheetId
sheetId.description: The sheet this span is on.

filterId.name: filterId
filterId.description: The ID of the filter being duplicated.

DuplicateFilterViewResponse.name: DuplicateFilterViewResponse
DuplicateFilterViewResponse.description: The result of a filter view being duplicated.

DuplicateSheetRequest.name: DuplicateSheetRequest
DuplicateSheetRequest.description: Duplicates the contents of a sheet.

insertSheetIndex.name: insertSheetIndex
insertSheetIndex.description:
The zero-based index where the new sheet should be inserted.
The index of all sheets after this are incremented.

newSheetName.name: newSheetName
newSheetName.description: The name of the new sheet.  If empty, a new name is chosen for you.

newSheetId.name: newSheetId
newSheetId.description:
If set, the ID of the new sheet. If not set, an ID is chosen.
If set, the ID must not conflict with any existing sheet ID.
If set, it must be non-negative.

DuplicateSheetResponse.name: DuplicateSheetResponse
DuplicateSheetResponse.description: The result of duplicating a sheet.

Editors.name: Editors
Editors.description: The editors of a protected range.

groups.name: groups
groups.description: The email addresses of groups with edit access to the protected range.

domainUsersCanEdit.name: domainUsersCanEdit
domainUsersCanEdit.description:
True if anyone in the document's domain has edit access to the protected
range.  Domain protection is only supported on documents within a domain.

users.name: users
users.description: The email addresses of users with edit access to the protected range.

EmbeddedChart.name: EmbeddedChart
EmbeddedChart.description: A chart embedded in a sheet.

EmbeddedObjectPosition.name: EmbeddedObjectPosition
EmbeddedObjectPosition.description: The position of an embedded object such as a chart.

newSheet.name: newSheet
newSheet.description:
If true, the embedded object will be put on a new sheet whose ID
is chosen for you. Used only when writing.

sheetId.name: sheetId
sheetId.description:
The sheet this is on. Set only if the embedded object
is on its own sheet. Must be non-negative.

message.name: message
message.description:
A message with more information about the error
(in the spreadsheet's locale).

ExtendedValue.name: ExtendedValue
ExtendedValue.description: The kinds of value that a cell in a spreadsheet can have.

stringValue.name: stringValue
stringValue.description:
Represents a string value.
Leading single quotes are not included. For example, if the user typed
`'123` into the UI, this would be represented as a `stringValue` of
`"123"`.

numberValue.name: numberValue
numberValue.description:
Represents a double value.
Note: Dates, Times and DateTimes are represented as doubles in
"serial number" format.

FilterCriteria.name: FilterCriteria
FilterCriteria.description: Criteria for showing/hiding rows in a filter or filter view.

filterViewId.name: filterViewId
filterViewId.description: The ID of the filter view.

sortSpecs.name: sortSpecs
sortSpecs.description:
The sort order per column. Later specifications are used when values
are equal in the earlier specifications.

namedRangeId.name: namedRangeId
namedRangeId.description:
The named range this filter view is backed by, if any.

When writing, only one of range or named_range_id
may be set.

criteria.name: criteria
criteria.description:
The criteria for showing/hiding values per column.
The map's key is the column index, and the value is the criteria for
that column.

title.name: title
title.description: The name of the filter view.

FindReplaceRequest.name: FindReplaceRequest
FindReplaceRequest.description: Finds and replaces data in cells over a range, sheet, or all sheets.

searchByRegex.name: searchByRegex
searchByRegex.description:
True if the find value is a regex.
The regular expression and replacement should follow Java regex rules
at https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/regex/Pattern.html.
The replacement string is allowed to refer to capturing groups.
For example, if one cell has the contents `"Google Sheets"` and another
has `"Google Docs"`, then searching for `"o.* (.*)"` with a replacement of
`"$1 Rocks"` would change the contents of the cells to
`"GSheets Rocks"` and `"GDocs Rocks"` respectively.

matchCase.name: matchCase
matchCase.description: True if the search is case sensitive.

includeFormulas.name: includeFormulas
includeFormulas.description:
True if the search should include cells with formulas.
False to skip cells with formulas.

matchEntireCell.name: matchEntireCell
matchEntireCell.description: True if the find value should match the entire cell.

allSheets.name: allSheets
allSheets.description: True to find/replace over all sheets.

replacement.name: replacement
replacement.description: The value to use as the replacement.

valuesChanged.name: valuesChanged
valuesChanged.description: The number of non-formula cells changed.

occurrencesChanged.name: occurrencesChanged
occurrencesChanged.description:
The number of occurrences (possibly multiple within a cell) changed.
For example, if replacing `"e"` with `"o"` in `"Google Sheets"`, this would
be `"3"` because `"Google Sheets"` -> `"Googlo Shoots"`.

formulasChanged.name: formulasChanged
formulasChanged.description: The number of formula cells changed.

GradientRule.name: GradientRule
GradientRule.description:
A rule that applies a gradient color scale format, based on
the interpolation points listed. The format of a cell will vary
based on its contents as compared to the values of the interpolation
points.

GridCoordinate.name: GridCoordinate
GridCoordinate.description:
A coordinate in a sheet.
All indexes are zero-based.

sheetId.name: sheetId
sheetId.description: The sheet this coordinate is on.

rowIndex.name: rowIndex
rowIndex.description: The row index of the coordinate.

columnIndex.name: columnIndex
columnIndex.description: The column index of the coordinate.

GridData.name: GridData
GridData.description: Data in the grid, as well as metadata about the dimensions.

startRow.name: startRow
startRow.description: The first row this GridData refers to, zero-based.

columnMetadata.name: columnMetadata
columnMetadata.description:
Metadata about the requested columns in the grid, starting with the column
in start_column.

startColumn.name: startColumn
startColumn.description: The first column this GridData refers to, zero-based.

rowData.name: rowData
rowData.description:
The data in the grid, one entry per row,
starting with the row in startRow.
The values in RowData will correspond to columns starting
at start_column.

rowMetadata.name: rowMetadata
rowMetadata.description:
Metadata about the requested rows in the grid, starting with the row
in start_row.

frozenRowCount.name: frozenRowCount
frozenRowCount.description: The number of rows that are frozen in the grid.

frozenColumnCount.name: frozenColumnCount
frozenColumnCount.description: The number of columns that are frozen in the grid.

hideGridlines.name: hideGridlines
hideGridlines.description: True if the grid isn't showing gridlines in the UI.

rowCount.name: rowCount
rowCount.description: The number of rows in the grid.

columnCount.name: columnCount
columnCount.description: The number of columns in the grid.

GridRange.name: GridRange
GridRange.description:
A range on a sheet.
All indexes are zero-based.
Indexes are half open, e.g the start index is inclusive
and the end index is exclusive -- [start_index, end_index).
Missing indexes indicate the range is unbounded on that side.

For example, if `"Sheet1"` is sheet ID 0, then:

  `Sheet1!A1:A1 == sheet_id: 0,
                  start_row_index: 0, end_row_index: 1,
                  start_column_index: 0, end_column_index: 1`

  `Sheet1!A3:B4 == sheet_id: 0,
                  start_row_index: 2, end_row_index: 4,
                  start_column_index: 0, end_column_index: 2`

  `Sheet1!A:B == sheet_id: 0,
                start_column_index: 0, end_column_index: 2`

  `Sheet1!A5:B == sheet_id: 0,
                 start_row_index: 4,
                 start_column_index: 0, end_column_index: 2`

  `Sheet1 == sheet_id:0`

The start index must always be less than or equal to the end index.
If the start index equals the end index, then the range is empty.
Empty ranges are typically not meaningful and are usually rendered in the
UI as `#REF!`.

endColumnIndex.name: endColumnIndex
endColumnIndex.description: The end column (exclusive) of the range, or not set if unbounded.

endRowIndex.name: endRowIndex
endRowIndex.description: The end row (exclusive) of the range, or not set if unbounded.

sheetId.name: sheetId
sheetId.description: The sheet this range is on.

startColumnIndex.name: startColumnIndex
startColumnIndex.description: The start column (inclusive) of the range, or not set if unbounded.

startRowIndex.name: startRowIndex
startRowIndex.description: The start row (inclusive) of the range, or not set if unbounded.

InsertDimensionRequest.name: InsertDimensionRequest
InsertDimensionRequest.description: Inserts rows or columns in a sheet at a particular index.

inheritFromBefore.name: inheritFromBefore
inheritFromBefore.description:
Whether dimension properties should be extended from the dimensions
before or after the newly inserted dimensions.
True to inherit from the dimensions before (in which case the start
index must be greater than 0), and false to inherit from the dimensions
after.

For example, if row index 0 has red background and row index 1
has a green background, then inserting 2 rows at index 1 can inherit
either the green or red background.  If `inheritFromBefore` is true,
the two new rows will be red (because the row before the insertion point
was red), whereas if `inheritFromBefore` is false, the two new rows will
be green (because the row after the insertion point was green).

InterpolationPoint.name: InterpolationPoint
InterpolationPoint.description:
A single interpolation point on a gradient conditional format.
These pin the gradient color scale according to the color,
type and value chosen.

type.name: type
type.description: How the value should be interpreted.

value.name: value
value.description:
The value this interpolation point uses.  May be a formula.
Unused if type is MIN or
MAX.

MergeCellsRequest.name: MergeCellsRequest

mergeType.name: mergeType

The zero-based start index of where to move the source data to,
based on the coordinates *before* the source data is removed
from the grid.  Existing data will be shifted down or right
(depending on the dimension) to make room for the moved dimensions.
The source dimensions are removed from the grid, so the
the data may end up in a different index than specified.

For example, given `A1..A5` of `0, 1, 2, 3, 4` and wanting to move
`"1"` and `"2"` to between `"3"` and `"4"`, the source would be
`ROWS [1..3)`,and the destination index would be `"4"`
(the zero-based index of row 5).
The end result would be `A1..A5` of `0, 3, 1, 2, 4`.

RepeatCellRequest.name: RepeatCellRequest
RepeatCellRequest.description:
Updates all cells in the range to the values in the given Cell object.
Only the fields listed in the fields field are updated; others are
unchanged.

If writing a cell with a formula, the formula's ranges will automatically
increment for each field in the range.
For example, if writing a cell with formula `=A1` into range B2:C4,
B2 would be `=A1`, B3 would be `=A2`, B4 would be `=A3`,
C2 would be `=B1`, C3 would be `=B2`, C4 would be `=B3`.

To keep the formula's ranges static, use the `$` indicator.
For example, use the formula `=$A$1` to prevent both the row and the
column from incrementing.

methods.description:
Returns the spreadsheet at the given ID.
The caller must specify the spreadsheet ID.

By default, data within grids will not be returned.
You can include grid data one of two ways:

* Specify a field mask listing your desired fields using the `fields` URL
parameter in HTTP

* Set the includeGridData
URL parameter to true.  If a field mask is set, the `includeGridData`
parameter is ignored

For large spreadsheets, it is recommended to retrieve only the specific
fields of the spreadsheet that you want.

To retrieve only subsets of the spreadsheet, use the
ranges URL parameter.
Multiple ranges can be specified.  Limiting the range will
return only the portions of the spreadsheet that intersect the requested
ranges. Ranges are specified using A1 notation.

Appends values to a spreadsheet. The input range is used to search for
existing data and find a "table" within that range. Values will be
appended to the next row of the table, starting with the first column of
the table. See the
[guide](/sheets/guides/values#appending_values)
and
[sample code](/sheets/samples/writing#append_values)
for specific details of how tables are detected and data is appended.

The caller must specify the spreadsheet ID, range, and
a valueInputOption.  The `valueInputOption` only
controls how the input data will be added to the sheet (column-wise or
row-wise), it does not influence what cell the data starts being written
to.

`[[1,2],[3,4]]`,

methods.description:
Returns one or more ranges of values from a spreadsheet.
The caller must specify the spreadsheet ID and one or more ranges.

Applies one or more updates to the spreadsheet.

Each request is validated before
being applied. If any request is not valid then the entire request will
fail and nothing will be applied.

Some requests have replies to
give you some information about how
they are applied. The replies will mirror the requests.  For example,
if you applied 4 updates and the 3rd one had a reply, then the
response will have 2 empty replies, the actual reply, and another empty
reply, in that order.

Due to the collaborative nature of spreadsheets, it is not guaranteed that
the spreadsheet will reflect exactly your changes after this completes,
however it is guaranteed that the updates in the request will be
applied together atomically. Your changes may be altered with respect to
collaborator changes. If there are no collaborators, the spreadsheet
should reflect your changes.

spreadsheetId.name: spreadsheetId
spreadsheetId.description: The spreadsheet to apply the updates to.
